#: src/mathlib.c:788
msgid "Mathlib Benchmark Help"
msgstr "_Pomoć za Mathlib benchmark"

#: src/mathlib.c:790
msgid ""
"Jobs are forked and run in parallel by xnec2c, whereas threads are used by "
"the mathlib implementation to parallelize the linear algebra calculation of "
"one job.  For parallel algorithms you can reduce the number of threads in "
"use by the algorithm with the following environment variables:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# OpenBLAS thread limit\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# OpenMP thread limit\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Intel MKL thread limit\n"
"\n"
"Each benchmark specifies a complexity to indicate approximately how long it "
"will take to run.  For example, O(N) means the time will scale with N and "
"O(N*J) means it will scale with N*J:\n"
"  * N is the number of mathlibs selected here:\n"
"      File->Mathlib Benchmarks->Selected Mathlibs\n"
"  * J is the number of jobs specified on the command line with -j (eg, -j "
"8)\n"
"\n"
"Higher complexity options run more benchmarks to provide additional "
"information about how you might optimize your xnec2c runtime.  The benchmark "
"menu options are as follows:  \n"
"\n"
"* Parallel (-j N): O(N/J) time: Benchmark each mathlib in parallel with the "
"number of jobs specified on the command line with -j.\n"
"\n"
"* Single Job (-j 1): O(N) time: Benchmark each mathlib with a single job "
"even if -j was specified on the command line. This is useful to find the "
"fastest interactive mathlib that is used when the frequency is changed in "
"the UI by changing a Frequency MHz +/- widget or (right-)clicking on the "
"frequency plot\n"
"\n"
"* Iterate -j N/=2: O(N*log2(J)) time: Benchmark each mathlib in parallel "
"initially with the number of jobs specified on the command line with -j, and "
"then reduce the number jobs by half for each subsequent iteration until only "
"one job remains.  This is useful to find a balance between the number of "
"parallel jobs specified by -j and the number of threads used by the linear "
"algebra library as modified by the environment variables listed above.\n"
"\n"
"* Iterate -j N-=2: O(N*J) time: Same as -j N/=2 above, but instead decrement "
"the number of jobs by 1.  This takes the longest to run.\n"
msgstr ""
"Poslovi se granaju i pokreću paralelno u xnec2c, dok dretve koristi "
"implementacija Mathlib knjižnice za paralelizaciju izračuna linearne algebre "
"jednog posla. Za paralelne algoritme možete smanjiti broj dretvi koje "
"koristi algoritam sljedećim varijablama okoline:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# Ograničenje dretvi OpenBLAS\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Ograničenje dretvi OpenMP\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Ograničenje dretvi Intel MKL\n"
"\n"
"Svako mjerenje performansi navodi složenost kako bi okvirno pokazalo koliko "
"dugo će trajati. Na primjer, O(N) znači da će vrijeme rasti s N, a O(N*J) "
"znači da će rasti s N*J:\n"
"  * N je broj Mathlib knjižnica odabranih ovdje:\n"
"      File->Mathlib Benchmarks->Selected Mathlibs\n"
"  * J je broj poslova naveden na naredbenom retku s -j (npr. -j 8)\n"
"\n"
"Opcije veće složenosti pokreću više mjerenja performansi radi pružanja "
"dodatnih informacija o tome kako optimizirati izvođenje xnec2c-a. Opcije "
"izbornika za mjerenje performansi su sljedeće:  \n"
"\n"
"* Paralelno (-j N): O(N/J) vremena: Mjeri svaku Mathlib knjižnicu paralelno "
"s brojem poslova navedenih na naredbenom retku s -j.\n"
"\n"
"* Jedan posao (-j 1): O(N) vremena: Mjeri svaku Mathlib knjižnicu s jednim "
"poslom čak i ako je -j naveden na naredbenom retku. Korisno za pronalazak "
"najbrže interaktivne Mathlib knjižnice koja se koristi kada se frekvencija "
"mijenja u sučelju promjenom widgeta Frequency MHz +/- ili (desnim) klikom na "
"grafikon frekvencija.\n"
"\n"
"* Iteracija -j N/=2: O(N*log2(J)) vremena: Mjeri svaku Mathlib knjižnicu "
"paralelno, početno s brojem poslova navedenih na naredbenom retku s -j, a "
"zatim prepolovi broj poslova za svaku sljedeću iteraciju dok ne ostane samo "
"jedan posao. Korisno za pronalazak ravnoteže između broja paralelnih poslova "
"zadanih s -j i broja dretvi koje koristi knjižnica linearne algebre prema "
"gore navedenim varijablama okoline.\n"
"\n"
"* Iteracija -j N-=2: O(N*J) vremena: Isto kao -j N/=2 gore, ali umjesto toga "
"smanjuje broj poslova za 1. Traje najdulje.\n"

#: src/mathlib.c:839 src/mathlib.c:846 src/mathlib.c:852 src/mathlib.c:869
#: src/mathlib.c:874 src/mathlib.c:981
msgid "Mathlib Benchmark"
msgstr "_Testovi performansi za Mathlib"

#: src/mathlib.c:840
msgid "Benchmarks are disabled while optimization is activated."
msgstr "Mjerenja performansi su onemogućena dok je optimizacija aktivna."

#: src/mathlib.c:847
msgid "You must load a NEC2 input file before running benchmarks."
msgstr ""
"Morate učitati NEC2 ulaznu datoteku prije pokretanja mjerenja performansi."

#: src/mathlib.c:853
msgid ""
"Choosing a benchmark other than \"Single Job\" has no effect unless -j is "
"specified on the command line."
msgstr ""
"Odabir mjerenja performansi osim \"Jedan posao\" nema učinka ako -j nije "
"naveden na naredbenom retku."

#: src/mathlib.c:870
msgid "You must select at least one math library to benchmark"
msgstr ""
"Morate odabrati barem jednu matematičku knjižnicu za mjerenje performansi"

#: src/mathlib.c:875
#, c-format
msgid ""
"This will run a frequency loop benchmark for each detected linear algebra "
"library and then provide a summary.  It may take some time to complete "
"depending on how big and how many frequencies your NEC2 will use. Detailed "
"timing will be provided in the terminal.\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"* Only one Intel MKL library can be tested without restarting xnec2c, so "
"select which one you wish to benchmark before proceeding or it will choose "
"the first in the list and skip the rest.\n"
"\n"
"* Thread congestion will occur for multi-threaded libraries when using the -"
"j N option if there are not enough CPUs available to accommodate the forked "
"processes in combination with library threads.  Consider reducing the value "
"of -j N for benchmarking to find what library works best with a mix of "
"forking and threading; you can use `top` to monitor your CPU usageand if it "
"reaches 0%% idle then you might consider reducing -j N.\n"
"\n"
"You may wish to experiment setting these environment variables:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# OpenBLAS thread limit\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# OpenMP thread limit\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Intel MKL thread limit\n"
"\n"
"Click OK to proceed, this dialog will close when complete."
msgstr ""
"Ovo će pokrenuti mjerenje frekvencijske petlje za svaku otkrivenu knjižnicu "
"linearne algebre i zatim pružiti sažetak.  Može potrajati neko vrijeme "
"ovisno o veličini i broju frekvencija koje vaš NEC2 koristi. Detaljna "
"mjerenja bit će prikazana u terminalu.\n"
"\n"
"Napomene:\n"
"* Samo jedna Intel MKL knjižnica može biti testirana bez ponovnog pokretanja "
"xnec2c, stoga odaberite koju želite testirati prije nastavka ili će odabrati "
"prvu u popisu i preskočiti ostale.\n"
"\n"
"* Zagušenje dretvi pojavit će se za višedretvene knjižnice pri korištenju "
"opcije -j N ako nema dovoljno CPU-ova za prihvat razgranatih procesa u "
"kombinaciji s dretvama knjižnica.  Razmislite o smanjenju -j N za mjerenje "
"da biste pronašli koja knjižnica najbolje radi; možete koristiti `top` za "
"praćenje korištenja CPU-a i ako dosegne 0%% praznog vremena smanjite -j N.\n"
"\n"
"Možda biste željeli eksperimentirati postavljanjem ovih varijabli okoline:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# Ograničenje dretvi OpenBLAS\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Ograničenje dretvi OpenMP\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Ograničenje dretvi Intel MKL\n"
"\n"
"Kliknite OK za nastavak, ovaj dijaloški okvir će se zatvoriti po završetku."

